As I understand it, SA-1 was supposed to be in the Super NES CD-ROM system cartridge. But when Nintendo dismissed each of its partners, they switched to an instruction set that had more of a future. Philips made CD-i (all toasters toast toast!) with a customized 68000-based CPU, while Sony used MIPS for the PlayStation.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Aug 18, 2009 5:17 am</p><hr />
