Ah, yes. Replace the S-CPU with the 10.5MHz SA-1, but keep the HDMA. With I-RAM you can access in one cycle at that rate, and automatic bitmap-&gt;bitplane DMA transformation, software scaling would be trivial.<br /><br />Sadly, none of the SA-1 games really took advantage of the power of that chip.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=375">byuu</a> — Mon Aug 17, 2009 9:19 pm</p><hr />
